// Integer-arithmetic tautology: exercises polynomial/monomial normalisation and the
// introduction-time ordering features, i.e. the eviction/history-sensitive caches
// (monomialCache, polynomialCache, introductionTimeCache) that the propositional/FOL
// corpus problems do not touch. This is the case where a subtle cache bug would surface.
\problem {
    \forall int x; \forall int y; \forall int z;
        ((x + y) * z = x * z + y * z)
}
